==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Introsusception
<hw>In`tro*sus*cep"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act or process of receiving within.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The person is corrupted by the <qex>introsusception</qex> of a
nature which becomes evil thereby.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Same as
<er>Intussusception</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Introvenient</ent>⟦br⟧
